This is for spinning up 2 EC2 machines and web servers on it within an Auto scaling group and a load balancer in front of it.

Pre-requisites:
1. Terraform installed
2. AWS Account created
3. AWS User created with below policies configured.

AmazonEC2FullAccess
AmazonS3FullAccess
AmazonDynamoDBFullAccess
AmazonRDSFullAccess
CloudWatchFullAccess
IAMFullAccess

4. AWS Access Key Id and AWS Secret configured as environment variables

$ export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxx
$ export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxx

5. Run terraform commands

$ terraform init
$ terraform plan
$ terraform apply

Outputs:

aws_dns_name = "terraform-asg-example-2079044295.us-east-2.elb.amazonaws.com"

6. Test

$ curl http://terraform-asg-example-2079044295.us-east-2.elb.amazonaws.com/
Hello, world multi server!
